cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with grammar induction from text data. It could also belong to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves unsupervised learning of probabilistic models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) because it deals with speech data, and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) because it involves bounding the depth of recursion in the grammar induction model.
